  <ethicsAndSummary>
    <summary>Patients being referred for palliative care have high levels of anxiety and significant informational and emotional needs. Previous research suggests these needs are not always met. Provision of a question prompt list (QPL) to cancer patients before initial oncology consultations has been found to promote patient question asking, reduce anxiety, improve recall and shorten the consultation.  We have developed a QPL specifically for palliative care patients. We will study the effects of providing patients with this QPL before their consultation with a palliative care doctor.</summary>
